{{Infobox video game |title = Boogie Bunnies |image = BoogieBunnieslogo.jpg |developer = [[Artech Studios]] |publisher = [[Vivendi Games]]{{efn|Released under the [[Sierra Online]] brand name}} |released = January 16, 2008 |genre = [[Puzzle game]] |modes = [[Single player]], [[Multiplayer video game|Multiplayer]] |platforms = [[Xbox 360]], [[Windows]] }}
'''''Boogie Bunnies''''' is a match-3 [[puzzle game]] developed by Artech Studios for the [[Xbox 360|Xbox 360's]] [[Xbox Live Arcade]] service and [[Windows]]. The game features same machine and [[Xbox Live]] co-op multiplayer. The title was released on January 16, 2008.<ref>{{cite web| author = Brandon Boyer | title = Xbox Live Arcade To Get Boogie Bunnies | publisher = [[Gamasutra]] | date = 2008-01-14 | url = http://www.gamasutra.com/php-bin/news_index.php?story=16942 }}</ref>
==Reception== [[Image:boogiebunniesgameplay.jpg|thumb|left|''Boogie Bunnies'' gameplay screenshot|150px]]
{{Video game reviews | GR = 57.61%<ref name=GR/> | MC = 54/100<ref name=MC/> | TX = 7.5/10<ref name=TXbox/> | IGN = 4.1/10<ref name=IGN/> | GSpot = 6.5/10<ref name=GSpot>{{Cite web |url=https://www.gamespot.com/reviews/boogie-bunnies-review/1900-6184884/ |title=Boogie Bunnies Review |website=[[GameSpot]] |publisher=CBS Interactive |date=January 18, 2008 |last=Thomas |first=Aaron |accessdate=September 19, 2018}}</ref> | EuroG = 6/10<ref name=EuroG>{{Cite web |url=https://www.eurogamer.net/articles/xbox-live-arcade-roundup-review |title=Xbox Live Arcade Roundup |website=[[Eurogamer]] |publisher=[[Gamer Network]] |date=February 13, 2008 |last=Parkin |first=Simon |accessdate=September 19, 2018}}</ref> | OXM = 4.5/10<ref name=OXM>{{Cite web |url=http://www.oxmonline.com/article/reviews/xbox-live-arcade/a-f/boogie-bunnies |title=Boogie Bunnies |work=[[Official Xbox Magazine]] |date=January 16, 2008 |last=Amrich |first=Dan |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20080118040927/http://www.oxmonline.com/article/reviews/xbox-live-arcade/a-f/boogie-bunnies |archivedate=January 18, 2008 |accessdate=September 19, 2018}}</ref> | GamePro = 2.25/5<ref name=GPro>{{Cite web |url=http://www.gamepro.com/microsoft/xbox360/games/reviews/165968.shtml |title=Review: Boogie Bunnies for Xbox 360 |work=[[GamePro]] |publisher=[[IDG]] |date=March 3, 2008 |last=Dagley |first=Andrew |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20080508024530/http://www.gamepro.com/microsoft/xbox360/games/reviews/165968.shtml |archivedate=May 8, 2008 |accessdate=September 19, 2018}}</ref> }}
''Boogie Bunnies'' received mixed to negative reviews from critics upon release. On [[Metacritic]], the game holds a score of 54/100 based on 19 reviews, indicating "mixed or average reviews."<ref name=MC>{{Cite web |url=https://www.metacritic.com/game/xbox-360/boogie-bunnies |title=Boogie Bunnies for Xbox 360 Reviews |website=[[Metacritic]] |publisher=[[CBS Interactive]] |accessdate=September 19, 2018}}</ref> On [[GameRankings]], the game holds a score of 57.61% based on 18 reviews.<ref name=GR>{{Cite web |url=https://www.gamerankings.com/xbox360/943662-boogie-bunnies/index.html |title=Boogie Bunnies for Xbox 360 |website=[[GameRankings]] |publisher=CBS Interactive |accessdate=September 19, 2018}}</ref>
[[Team Xbox]] scored the game a 7.5 out of 10 stating, "Despite a few bungled dance steps here and there, ''Boogie Bunnies'' is still a strangely addictive experience."<ref name=TXbox>{{cite web | url=http://reviews.teamxbox.com/xbox-360/1458/Boogie-Bunnies/p1/ | title=Team Xbox: Boogie Bunnies Review (Xbox 360) | author=David Chapman | publisher=[[Team Xbox]] | date=2008-01-15 | deadurl=yes | archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20080116223911/http://reviews.teamxbox.com/xbox-360/1458/Boogie-Bunnies/p1/ | archivedate=2008-01-16 | df= }}</ref> [[IGN]] criticized the game saying "It does nothing different from the gaggle of puzzlers that are already out there and the old playstyles that it employs aren't nearly as fun as we'd hoped."<ref name=IGN>{{cite web | url=http://xbox360.ign.com/articles/845/845747p1.html | title=IGN: Boogie Bunnies Review | author=Nate Ahearn | publisher=[[IGN]] | date=2008-01-15 | deadurl=yes | archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20080119132429/http://xbox360.ign.com/articles/845/845747p1.html | archivedate=2008-01-19 | df= }}</ref>
Boogie Bunnies was nominated for one Xbox Live Arcade 2008 award, "Best Family Game".<ref>[http://kotaku.com/5161442/vote-in-the-2008-xbox-live-arcade-awards Vote In The Xbox Live Arcade 2008 Awards], Kotaku.com. Fetched 3/24/2009.</ref> {{Clear}}
