'''Mark II''' is a rideable and user-operated [[robot]] built by the American company [[MegaBots Inc.]] The robot made its debut in May 2015 at [[Maker Faire]] San Mateo. An updated version of the robot, Mk.III, is scheduled in August 2017 to engage in a head-to-head fight with [[Kuratas]], a robot built by Suidobashi Heavy Industry of Japan.<ref>[https://www.theverge.com/2015/8/18/9165459/giant-robot-fight-megabots-kickstarter Team USA launches Kickstarter to fund its giant robot duel with Japan]</ref><ref>[http://www.livescience.com/51909-megabots-battle-robot-photos.html Massive 'Battle Bot' Gears Up for Robot Duel]</ref><ref>[http://www.livescience.com/51918-megabots-fighting-robot-kickstarter.html Giant 'Battle Bot' Could Get Makeover Ahead of Epic Duel]</ref> MegaBots announced plans in August 2015 to upgrade Mark II with melee capabilities in order to confront Kuratas, using funds from a [[Kickstarter]] campaign.<ref>[http://edition.cnn.com/2015/07/07/tech/giant-robot-fight-challenge-accepted USA vs. Japan Part II: Giant robots set to duel]</ref><ref>[http://time.com/4003407/giant-robot-fight-megabots-japan/ A Team of Americans Is Building a Giant Robot to Challenge Japan In Hand to Hand Combat]</ref><ref>[https://www.kickstarter.com/projects/megabots/support-team-usa-in-the-giant-robot-duel MegaBots Kickstarter Campaign]</ref>
