'''Nòva cançon''' ({{IPA-oc|ˈnɔβɔ kanˈsu, -ɔvɔ}}, also spelled ''Nòva chançon'' {{IPA-oc|ˈnɔvɔ tʃanˈsu|}}, "New Song") is a musical renewal wave that swept through [[Occitania]] in the 1970s. Its leaders were [[Joan Pau Verdier]], [[Claudi Martí]], [[Patric]], [[Maria Roanet]] and [[Mans de Breish]], most of whom are still very active singers. '''Nòva cançon''' was a phenomenon similar to [[Catalonia]]'s [[Nova cançó]].

