The {{nihongo|'''Toyota Municipal Museum of Art'''|豊田市美術館|Toyota-shi Bijutsukan}} is an [[art museum]] located in the city of [[Toyota, Aichi|Toyota]], [[Aichi Prefecture]], [[Japan]].
== History == The museum features works by [[Gustav Klimt]], [[Egon Schiele]], [[Edvard Munch]], and others. The museum building was constructed by [[Yoshio Taniguchi]], who also renovated the [[Museum of Modern Art]] (MoMA) in New York City.
Artists who have exhibited are [[Leiko Ikemura]].
Public transport is with the [[Mikawa Line]] to [[Toyotashi Station]].
